## **Detailed Example 1**

### **Input:**
```python
root = [3, 9, 20, null, null, 15, 7]
```

### **Tree Structure:**
```
        3
       / \
      9   20
         /  \
        15   7
```

### **Step-by-Step:**

**Level 0 (depth 0): →** (Left to Right)
```
        3
       / \
      9   20
         /  \
        15   7

Nodes at this level: [3]
Direction: → (left to right)
Result: [3]
```

**Level 1 (depth 1): ←** (Right to Left - REVERSED!)
```
        3
       / \
     [9] [20]  ← Process right to left
         /  \
        15   7

Nodes at this level: [9, 20]
Direction: ← (right to left)
Reversed: [20, 9]
Result: [3, 20, 9]
```

**Level 2 (depth 2): →** (Left to Right)
```
        3
       / \
      9   20
         /  \
       [15] [7]  → Process left to right

Nodes at this level: [15, 7]
Direction: → (left to right)
Result: [3, 20, 9, 15, 7]
```

### **Output:**
```python
[[3], [20, 9], [15, 7]]

# Or as flat list:
[3, 20, 9, 15, 7]
```

